<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!--
	  Project Whisper — Hardened Runtime entitlements (macOS notarization)

	  Scope: this is a PURE GDScript Godot 4.5 game (renderer = gl_compatibility),
	  with NO C# / Mono, NO GDExtension / native add-ons, NO camera / microphone /
	  location / address-book / calendar usage. The entitlement set is therefore the
	  MINIMUM that a notarized Godot game needs — everything not required is omitted
	  on purpose (Apple rejects over-broad entitlements and each one widens the
	  attack surface).

	  Deliberately OMITTED and why:
	    * com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit
	    * com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory
	    * com.apple.security.cs.allow-dyld-environment-variables
	        GDScript runs on a bytecode INTERPRETER, not a JIT. Godot's own macOS
	        export docs enable these ONLY for Mono/C# builds or native add-ons that
	        emit/patch executable memory. This build has neither, so they stay off.
	    * com.apple.security.get-task-allow  (Debugging)
	        MUST be off for notarization — Apple rejects apps that ship it.
	    * device/privacy entitlements (audio-input, camera, location, ...)
	        The game accesses none of these.
	    * App Sandbox (com.apple.security.app-sandbox)
	        Only required for the Mac App Store, NOT for Developer-ID + notarization
	        direct distribution (our path). Left off intentionally.

	  KEPT:
	    * com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation
	        Godot loads its game data (Resources/ProjectWhisper.pck) and the export
	        template links its universal Mach-O slices; with Hardened Runtime this
	        entitlement lets the process map that content without a library-validation
	        rejection. Godot's macOS docs recommend it for ad-hoc-signed and
	        add-on-loading exports; it is the single safe minimal entitlement here.
	-->
	<key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
	<true/>
</dict>
</plist>
